    <item>
      <title>Deciding what to decide is no easy task</title>
      <link>/post/deciding-what-to-decide/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 13 Dec 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>/post/deciding-what-to-decide/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;With warm and sunny days becoming more frequent, do you struggle to stay motivated to work throughout the day?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I sure do!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;During the summer I often argue with myself: should I keep working or take a break and go outside to take advantage of the beautiful weather?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;More often than not, I keep working until something tells me that’s its time for a break, and I get to enjoy the sun.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But what’s that something inside me that tells me why I should keep working or when to take a break?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Click &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.concordia.ca/cunews/offices/vprgs/sgs/public-scholars-21/2021/05/13/deciding-what-to-decide-is-no-easy-task.html&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; to keep reading.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
